--- ============================================================
--- run_bigstep_tests.maude
--- ============================================================
--- Loads the pythonlite big-step semantics + named test programs and
--- rewrites each one to a final < Sigma, Out > configuration.  The
--- shell-level driver [`run_diff_test.sh`] parses the printed Out
--- buffer back into newline-separated integers and diffs against
--- CPython's stdout for the same Python source.
--- ============================================================

in builtins.maude
in pythonlite-syntax.maude
in pythonlite-state.maude
in pythonlite-bigstep.maude
in pythonlite-programs.maude

mod TEST is
  including PYTHONLITE-SEMANTICS-BIGSTEP + PYTHONLITE-PROGRAMS .
endm

--- Each `rewrite < <name>Pgm > .` line emits a single
--- `< Sigma:State, Out:Out >` configuration; the shell driver greps
--- the `Out` portion [the `_::_` integer list] for comparison.

rewrite < smokePgm > .
rewrite < arithPgm > .
rewrite < ifPgm > .
rewrite < factorialPgm > .
rewrite < collatzPgm > .
rewrite < fizzbuzzPgm > .
rewrite < shortcircPgm > .

quit
